724039f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Square South - Wooster Street
724039f-a.text:
76 Wsashington Sduare South (formerly 290 4th Street) at the S.W. corner
of Wooster Street (WWashington SQuare East). This is supoosed to
be the oldest house now standing on Washington Square.
Washington Square South is part of 4th Street as originally laid out.
In 1833, when 4th Street absorbed Asylum Street in Greenwich Villsge,
the whole was renumbered from the northwest end at Garnsevoort and
13th Streets. About 1860 the section from MacDougal to Wooster
Streets was given its own house hhnumbers as Washington Square South.
October 4, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
